# Verify that ffiStaticLink := true reflects in the cc command line.
# We dump the command to a file (dumpCcCommand) and grep for the GNU ld / lld
# static toggle the plugin folds the named link libs in with
# (`-Wl,-Bstatic <libs> -Wl,-Bdynamic`). A bare `-static` is intentionally NOT
# emitted: it would pull libc.a into a `-shared` link and ld would fail.
# Running ffiCompile directly would break on macOS; flag plumbing is the
# property under test here.
> dumpCcCommand
$ exists target/cc-cmd.txt
$ exec grep -- '-Wl,-Bstatic' target/cc-cmd.txt
